      • checkPreConditions_ServerResponse

        public void checkPreConditions_ServerResponse(java.lang.Object object)
        checkPreConditions_ServerResponse
        public void checkPreConditions_ServerResponse(Object object)
        This method is called after the server runs the query from checkPreConditions() and set values for the arguments of the class. if the conditions are not met it loads the PreValidationController page. if the conditions are met it runs the init() method.
        Parameters:
        object - holds the answer from the server after running the query

      • setValidationTable

        public void setValidationTable()
        setValidationTable
        public void setValidationTable()
        Is called on failureReportBtnClicked(ActionEvent) and send a query to the server in order to insert a new row in "Execution Failure Report" table. This method is linked with setValidationTable_ServerResponse(Object) method as it is the answer to the query.
